---
description: Frontend rules for React + TypeScript
globs: ["src/**/*.ts", "src/**/*.tsx"]
alwaysApply: true
---

Frontend stack:
- React
- TypeScript
- Tailwind
- Zustand
- TanStack Query

Rules:
- Use TypeScript strictly.
- Avoid any unless absolutely necessary.
- Prefer explicit prop types.
- Prefer small focused components.
- Keep container logic separate from presentational components when complexity grows.
- Keep components pure when possible.
- Avoid deep prop drilling; use composition or state hooks appropriately.
- Co-locate feature-specific hooks, components, and types inside the feature folder.
- Reusable primitives belong in shared/ui or components/ui.
- Avoid business logic inside JSX.
- Use memoization only when justified.
- Prefer readable code over clever code.

Data/state rules:
- TanStack Query for async command/query data
- Zustand for selected repo, selected commit, layout state, panel visibility
- do not duplicate the same source of truth in multiple stores

UI rules:
- UI must feel dense, fast, and professional
- follow a GitKraken/Fork-like information density
- prioritize keyboard-friendly interactions
- right panel is for AI/context intelligence
- left panel is for navigation/state
- center panel is for work area

When creating UI:
- include loading, empty, and error states
- never leave destructive actions without confirmation
- preserve dark-mode-friendly styling
- keep spacing and typography consistent